<p>Kareem Khalifa, currently professor of <a href="https://philosophy.ucla.edu/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">philosophy at the University of California, Los Angeles</a>, will be moving to the University of Pittsburgh, where he will be professor in the <a href="https://www.hps.pitt.edu/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Department of History and Philosophy of Science</a>.<span id="more-54835"></span></p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="alignnone wp-image-43532 aligncenter wp-dark-mode-bg-image" src="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/khalifa-kareem.jpeg" sizes="auto, (max-width: 485px) 100vw, 485px" srcset="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/khalifa-kareem.jpeg 485w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/khalifa-kareem-300x300.jpeg 300w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/khalifa-kareem-150x150.jpeg 150w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/khalifa-kareem-400x400.jpeg 400w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/khalifa-kareem-177x177.jpeg 177w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/khalifa-kareem-380x380.jpeg 380w" alt="" width="400" height="400" /></p>
<p>Professor Khalifa specializes in philosophy of science, philosophy of social science, epistemology, and philosophy of race. You can learn more about his research <a class="wp-dark-mode-bg-image" href="https://www.kareemkhalifa.com/research.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a> and <a class="wp-dark-mode-bg-image" href="https://philpeople.org/profiles/kareem-khalifa" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a>.</p>
<p>He will be taking up his new position at Pittsburgh in the Fall of 2027.</p><p>The post <a href="https://dailynous.com/2025/09/02/khalifa-from-ucla-to-pittsburgh/">Khalifa from UCLA to Pittsburgh</a> first appeared on <a href="https://dailynous.com">Daily Nous</a>.</p>